                                    consisting of 120 credits, 33 of which are dedicated to the major. Some major classes include Social Psychology, Health and Safety in the Workplace, Labor and Management Relations, Corporate Training and Development, Employment Law, Group Dynamics, and more. In addition, all students complete an integrated capstone, two upper-division management courses, and 21 credits of electives to tailor their coursework. Students without any transfer credit graduate in approximately 3.5 years, and students with transfer credits can expect to graduate on an accelerated timeframe. To accommodate students&#8217; schedules, new classes start monthly. Similar degrees from WIU include bachelor&#8217;s degrees in Management, IT Management, and an MBA. Note that the curriculum has been signed according to the HRCI guidelines in preparation for PHR certification. Upon graduation, students should be prepared to work in a variety of HR-related positions.
                                </p>
