                                <h3> 19. Franklin University</h3>
                                <p>
                                    <img src="../../wp-content/uploads/2013/09/franklin-university-computer-science-e1451670947803.jpg" alt="franklin-university-computer-science" width="125" height="125" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1515" /><br />
                                    Franklin University&#8217;s bachelor&#8217;s in Human Resources Management that consists of 124 semester hours, 24 of which are dedicated to the major. Required classes include HR Management, Staffing, Training and Development, Compensation and Benefits, Employee and Labor Relations, and a Strategic Human Resources capstone. In addition, students take a business core (28 hours) and 4 hours of electives. For students who have already completed a bachelor&#8217;s degree in another area, Franklin University offers a subsequent bachelor&#8217;s that excludes general education requirements and gives eligible an accelerated option. Students may also transfer up to 84 credits from previously-earned credits, further accelerating coursework. Franklin&#8217;s online learning network is available 24/7 and encourages collaborative learning. Students also benefit from Franklin&#8217;s flexible scheduling.
