                                </ul>
                                <h3> 20 (tied). Philadelphia University</h3>
                                <p>
                                    <img src="../../wp-content/uploads/2016/01/philadelphia_university-e1451671003423.jpg" alt="PhilUniversity.Horizontal.CMYK" width="125" height="33" class="alignright size-full wp-image-3191" /><br />
                                    Philadelphia University offers a BS in Human Resources Management consisting of 120 total undergraduate credits, 15 of which are dedicated to the HR major. These classes are Human Resource Management, Training and Development, Compensation and Benefits, Labor/ Management Relations, and Applied Research and Practice in Human Resource Management. Note that the track follows the guidelines of the Society for Human Resource Management. The program culminates in a hands-on portfolio project that requires students to create a HR plan for a professional work environment. To tailor degrees to students&#8217; specific needs and interests, several concentrations are available, and students with previous academic experience may transfer up to 30 credits to accelerate coursework. Philadelphia U leverages the dynamic Blackboard platform, which is available 24/7 and encourages an intimate, collaborative educational experience; and all courses deliver in accelerated 8-week modules six times per year. Depending on background, students typically complete a bachelor&#8217;s degree in 2-3 years.
                                </p>
